Description
This appendix extends the official SFI Group System (v7.12) with a structured classification of equipment and systems for emission reduction and energy efficiency on board ships. It covers equipment mandatory or recommended under MARPOL Annex VI (NOx, SOx), IMO EEXI and CII regulations, EU ETS and FuelEU Maritime.
No existing official SFI codes are overwritten. All extensions occupy confirmed unassigned code space.
📌 r4 scope note: This edition covers the Emission reduction and energy efficiency domain only. The following groups are deferred to the Q4-2026 release: Alternative and low-emission fuels (707), Cable laying and cargo handling (328, 454), Shore power OPS/HVSC (868, 875), Ballast water treatment and underwater vehicles (801, 901).
601Dual-Fuel & EEXI Extension601800–601900
Engine-mounted fuel gas and pilot fuel systems on dual-fuel main engines. Official range: 601000–601200. New codes from 601800.
Code	Name	Description
601800	ME Fuel Gas System	Engine-mounted fuel gas system for dual-fuel main engine
601810	ME Fuel Gas Injection Valve	Gas admission valves mounted on main engine
601820	ME Pilot Fuel System	Engine-mounted pilot fuel system for dual-fuel ignition
601830	ME Pilot Fuel Injection Valve	Pilot fuel injection valves mounted on main engine
601900	EPL — Engine Power Limitation Unit	Electronic or mechanical power limitation device for EEXI compliance
Comment on 601 — Dual-Fuel & EEXI Extension
634Shaft Power Limitation (EEXI)634900
Official SFI 634 covers CPP plants. Code 634900 covers shaft power limitation for EEXI compliance.
Code	Name	Description
634900	SHaPoLi — Shaft Power Limitation System	Shaft power monitoring and limitation device for EEXI compliance
Comment on 634 — Shaft Power Limitation (EEXI)
646WHR Steam Extension646100
WHR steam generators for energy efficiency improvement. Official range: 646001–646039. For WHR systems generating electrical power see group 668.
Code	Name	Description
646100	WHR Exhaust Boiler (HRSG)	Heat recovery steam generator from exhaust gas, primarily for energy efficiency improvement
Comment on 646 — WHR Steam Extension
668Waste Heat Power Recovery SystemsNew subgroup
Systems that convert waste heat from exhaust gases directly into electrical power. Distinct from 646 (steam boiler): these systems produce electricity.
Code	Name	Description
668001	WHR Power Turbine Unit	Power turbine for electrical power generation from exhaust gas flow
668010	ORC Energy Recovery Module	Organic Rankine Cycle module for heat-to-power conversion
668020	WHR Power System Control Unit	Automation and control package for WHR power recovery systems
Comment on 668 — Waste Heat Power Recovery Systems
